{
  "texts": [
    "Of course, a potential defence might be that an officer may argue along the opinions voiced via privacy rules.",
    "An entirely contrary opinion is that it could be in the strategic interest of an organisation to hide potential explanations.",
    "Table 5 shows the identified legal and ethical gaps based on the analysis.",
    "The gaps we identified are divided into three categories: (1) transparency, (2) accountability, and (3) liability.",
    "On a transparency level, we need more visibility over explanations supporting decisions."
  ]
}